name: integer_i16_maximum
description: |
  This is the maximum i16 value, 32767. Adding 1 produces the unrepresentable
  value 32768 and may trap, wrap to -32768, saturate, or be evaluated in a wider
  type. Its all-lower-bits-set encoding is also the last u16 value that can be
  converted to i16 without changing the mathematical value.
format: hex
decode-as: i16
pair:
  - with: one.input
    hint: tricky
  - with: ../u16/signed-maximum.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "signed-integer"
  - "i16"
  - "maximum"
  - "boundary"
  - "overflow"
  - "conversion"
  - "two's-complement"
---
ff 7f # 32767
